# TDD Rule

## Workflow (red -> green -> refactor)

1. Write the test first in `apps/api/__tests__/...`.
   - Test should fail first.
2. Implement the minimum code in `apps/api/*.ts` to pass.
3. Refactor while keeping tests green.

## Test Location Rules
- Mirror source folders under `apps/api/__tests__/`.
- Existing project uses `.test.js` files for tests, even when source is TypeScript.
- Keep path parity to make imports and mocks predictable.

Examples:
- `apps/api/controllers/admin.controller.ts` -> `apps/api/__tests__/controllers/admin.controller.test.js`
- `apps/api/models/user.model.ts` -> `apps/api/__tests__/models/user.model.test.js`
- `apps/api/routes/auth.routes.ts` -> `apps/api/__tests__/routes/auth.routes.test.js`

## Test Commands
- Root: `npm test` (delegates to `turbo run test`).
- API only: run tests from `apps/api` with `npm test`.
- For focused loops in API workspace: `npm run test:watch`.

## Test Structure
Recommended nesting:

```ts
describe('<fileName>', () => {
  describe('<methodName>', () => {
    it('<expected behavior>', async () => {
      // assertions
    });
  });
});
```

## Mocking Rules
- Mock Mongoose model modules in unit tests; avoid real DB calls unless integration behavior is explicitly required.
- Keep mocks at the top level of the test file and reset mocks between tests when needed.

## Do Not
- Do not implement before there is at least one failing test.
- Do not skip the initial failing assertion step.
- Do not bundle unrelated behavior changes into one test cycle.
